PN,44410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774296676
OL,3,CFrom dating app to cold-blooded murder
OL,5,FThe trial heard that the victim had
OL,6,Fsuffered a "horrendous beating".
OL,7,FCharles MacCreanor KC said: "Three
OL,8,Fstabs to the neck, multiple traumatic
OL,9,Fblows to her head. Injuries consistent
OL,10,Fwith throttling and choking of her
OL,11,Fneck. I'm sorry to say it, left with
OL,12,Fher face in a dog bowl, like an
OL,13,Fanimal".
OL,15,FMcCullagh is questioned by police
OL,16,Fabout the death. In his initial
OL,17,Finterview he tells police he was doing
OL,18,Fa livestream at the time of her death
OL,19,Fand that he believes Ms McNally's ex-
OL,20,Fboyfriend is the "only one that would
OL,21,Fharm her".
OL,26,@nD@LOUnD@_O]oD@]OUuD@GO]|D@ROU}D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774296676
OL,3,CFrom dating app to cold-blooded murder
OL,5,FHe is asked by police "Had you
OL,6,Fanything whatsoever to do with the
OL,7,Fdeath of Natalie?" to which replied:
OL,8,F"No comment". His solicitor tells him:
OL,9,F"Sorry, I think you could answer
OL,10,Fthat." McCullagh tells police "No, no,
OL,11,Fno comment."
OL,13,FDecember 20:
OL,15,F7.34am: McCullagh is released by
OL,16,Fpolice.
OL,18,FDecember 24: The McNally family are
OL,19,Ftold McCullagh is no longer a suspect
OL,20,Ffor the murder.
OL,26,@mD@WOUoD@RO]pD@AOUpD@LO]qD@AOUrD@FO]rD@
OL,26,A_OUsD@LO]
